{
  "texts": [
    "Third, they create fake dapp sites to phish users and misdirect wallet connections (Aladhadh et al., 2022; Xiong et al., 2023).",
    "Fourth, they build Ponzi schemes (Zheng et al., 2023; Yu et al., 2021; Wang et al., 2021a; Gupta et al., 2022; Zheng et al., 2023; Cai et al., 2023; Goswami et al., 2021) with smart contracts, paying early investors with funds from later ones until collapse when new investors stop.",
    "Anonymity and transparency help attackers build credibility.",
    "The complexity of smart contracts, coupled with blockchain properties like immutability enables these frauds.",
    "All these scenarios can be the root causes of fraud because of the immutability, irreversibility, and transparency of transactions on Ethereum."
  ]
}